      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2020-03-27</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-05-04T14:45:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>COVID-19 Correctional Facility Emergency Response Act of 2020</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a new grant program to help states and local governments prevent, detect, and stop the spread of COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) in correctional facilities.</p> <p>Specifically, the Department of Justice (DOJ) must award grants to states and local governments that release certain persons&#8212;persons who do not pose a serious risk or who meet certain criteria based on age or health&#8212;from correctional facilities. </p> <p>Additionally, DOJ must award grants to states and local governments that adopt cite-and-release procedures for suspects who do not pose a public safety risk.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
